      "description": "Voyager 1's cameras were switched off in 1990 after its 'Pale Blue Dot' photo, and NASA has been shutting down its remaining science instruments one by one to conserve its dwindling power supply -- the cosmic ray subsystem was turned off in February 2026 and the low-energy charged particle instrument in April 2026. As of mid-2026, only the magnetometer and Plasma Wave Subsystem are still switched on.",
